        "@type": "http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string",
        "@value": "DEFINITION: Relates an aspect to a unit group. The aspect can be measured using any of the members of the unit group."
      },
      {
        "@type": "http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string",
        "@value": "EXAMPLE: The aspect distance can have a unit group that includes the units meter, inch, foot, etc."
